The paper discusses deep generative modelling using flows, which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus of the paper is on reducing the dimensionality of the latent space in flow models, which is particularly relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also proposes an improved multi-scale architecture, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses likelihood contribution based factorization of dimensions, which is a topic related to information theory and falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
